                    <p class="govuk-body">Dear Sir or Madam</p>

                    <p class="govuk-body">On [DATE TBC] we updated the Get funding to improve animal health and welfare scheme to include reviews and follow-ups on more than one herd or flock.</p>

                    <p class="govuk-body">If you keep more than one herd or flock of a species from the list of eligible species – beef cattle, dairy cattle, pigs or sheep – the change may benefit you. Otherwise, it won’t affect you.</p>

                    <p class="govuk-body">About this change:</p>
                    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
                        <li>you can still have reviews and follow-ups on more than one species</li>
                        <li>you can have up to 3 reviews and 3 follow-ups for any number of herds or flocks of a species</li>
                        <li>your review and follow-up visits must be done by the 19 June 2027</li>
                    </ul>

                    <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-padding-top-6">Expressions used below shall have the same meaning as set out in your IAHW agreement unless defined.</p>

                    <h2 class="govuk-heading-s">What we've changed</h2>

                    <p class="govuk-body">The IAHW scheme has been expanded. You may now have up to 3 Reviews and 3 Follow-ups on any number of herds or flocks (epidemiologically distinct units) of one or more Species under your Agreement. Species means any of the following animals - beef cattle, dairy cattle, sheep and pigs.</p>

                    <h2 class="govuk-heading-s">What this means for you</h2>

                    <p class="govuk-body">
                    We are varying your Improve Animal Health and Welfare (IAHW) Agreement in line with condition 7 of your Agreement to include the changes above. Read the <a href="#">variations to the terms and conditions</a>.
                </p>

                    <h2 class="govuk-heading-s">
                    What you need to do    
                </h2>

                    <p class="govuk-body">
                    You don't need to do anything to accept this variation to your IAHW Agreement.
                </p>

                    <p class="govuk-body">
                    However, to make sure you have understood the changes we have made to your IAHW Agreement, you must read the <a href="#">variations to the terms and conditions</a> and the <a href="#">updated terms and conditions</a>.
                </p>

                    <p class="govuk-body">
                    If you want to reject the variation to your IAHW Agreement and continue with, or terminate, your existing IAHW Agreement, you must write to us by enter date.
                </p>

                    <p class="govuk-body">
                    If we do not hear from you by enter date, the variation will be accepted and your IAHW Agreement will be varied from the date you received this email.
                </p>

                    <h2 class="govuk-heading-s">If you have any questions about this email</h2>

                    <p class="govuk-body">
                    You can email <a href="#">ruralpayments@defra.gov.uk</a>, please include 'IAHW' in the subject line and tell us [your/your client's] SBI and IAHW agreement number, which are at the top of this email. Or, you can call us on 03000 200 301 (Monday to Friday, 8:30am to 5pm).
                </p>

                    <p class="govuk-body">
                   Yours faithfully
                </p>

